    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <head>No. 263.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Chang Yen
                                    Hoon</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 14, 1888</date>.
                                (Received May 14.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I had the honor to receive
                            your note of the 8th instant, informing me of the approval of the treaty
                            by the United States Senate, with two amendments, which you inclosed,
                            written in red ink on its margin, and to which I have already
                            replied.</p>
                <p>I have the honor now to acknowledge the receipt of your note of the 11th
                            instant, inclosing a full copy of the treaty and the two amendments, and
                            also the printed copy of the treaty, with the amendments noted in red
                            ink.</p>
                <p>I will, without delay, send them to the foreign office, which will
                            present them, with the original signed treaty, to the Throne for its
                            decree. I will communicate with you as soon as I am notified of the
                            decree. The amendments will be, in due form, noted in the certificate of
                            exchange of ratification.</p>
                <p>I am, very truly, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chang Yen
                                    Hoon.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
